# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored.

# ── Writing projects (the /words stories) ─────────────────────────────
# Base URL of the R2 bucket that serves story content over HTTPS
# (public bucket, custom domain, or a CDN/signing proxy in front).
# Server-only — NO `VITE_` prefix; read inside the server functions.
# Unset → the app falls back to the in-repo sample (src/content/stories.sample.ts).
#
# Expected object layout under the base URL:
#   <base>/catalog.json                 -> { "stories": [ { id, title, status, coverColor,
#                                            blurb, logline, tags, chapters, words, updated,
#                                            toc: [ { index, title, date, words, isNew?, read? } ] } ] }
#   <base>/<storyId>/<chapterId>.json   -> { "blocks": [ ...ChapterBody blocks ] }
#
# STORIES_R2_BASE_URL=https://stories.pauldolden.com
